Show HN: Non-AI created illustrations, crafted by human imagination
text:
Hi Hacker News community! I'm thrilled to introduce my wife, Diana, the creative mastermind behind absurd.design. As a team, we offer hand-drawn illustrations to project makers who appreciate free-spirited and quirky aesthetics.

In a time where technology is transforming artwork, Diana strongly believes that the love and emotion a human artist puts into their work cannot be replaced by anything else. That's why absurd.design illustrations are carefully crafted with love and dedication, designed to speak to the emotions of humans like you.

We're excited to share our latest project with you - Chapter 5. This collection features 30 hand-drawn illustrations that tell stories about everyday thoughts and emotions. We invite you to explore their expressive strokes and ignite your creativity.

If you resonate with Diana's work and want to add a touch of quirky aesthetics to your digital projects, we invite you to join our universe of absurd.design. We love sharing our newest works with project members and receiving feedback from the community.

Have you used absurd.design illustrations in your projects before? What led you to choose our platform? We'd love to hear your thoughts and suggestions. Thanks for reading!

Ask HN: A formula or library to generate color palettes?
text:
Use case: I'm building a feature that allows a User to ask for e.g. a "sky blue" design. From there I would have "sky blue" as the dominant color, but I need a library or "best practice formula" to generate hex codes for text, headers, bullet point icons, accent colors, etc.

I want to be able to generate a complete CSS color palette from just this one fuzzy ask. A palette is maybe 8+ colors and asking Users to pick each is just asking for trouble. (Even better if I can generate 3 palettes and let the user pick one).

Is there a great resource for this?
